==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dentirostral
<hw>Den`ti*ros"tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a toothed bill; -- applied to a group of passerine birds,
having the bill notched, and feeding chiefly on insects, as the shrikes
and vireos. See <xex>Illust.</xex> (<xex>N</xex>) under
<er>Beak</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dentirostrate</ent>⟦br⟧
